value.0: With gear suited to the cold and frozen surroundings, these well trained and keen eyed rangers look as though they would be able to almost disappear into the wild when needed. Acting as the eyes and ears of Forrstakkr, as well as the first line of defense, they are all dedicated to protecting the people of Forrstakkr from whatever may threaten.
This magic bow has a bonus to attack. As well, it allows the wielder to add part of his strength modifier to the damage dealt.

Hardened by the hostile environment, trained extensively and outfitted with high quality equipment, the men and women of the Forrstakkr Guard are a more than capable fighting force in the harsh northern environment. Augmented by veterans from the Ostland conflict, this force is quite ready to protect and fight for the people of Forrstakkr.

Predatory blue eyes keep careful watch on the surroundings, including you. One could not easily mistake this wolf for a dog. However, unlike its brethren which stalk the wilds this one seems to have been somewhat domesticated. While the guards of Forrstakkr have found a way to domesticate the wild wolves, it seems unlikely they would take as kindly to outsiders.

Vinni is the man who accepts every loaf of bread that High Priest Snorri sends from the Temple of Helm. Every time he sees a loaf of bread he turns a little green. Even to this day with Vinni having moved to Howness, Snorri still sends the bread, and Vinni still turns green.
Augir is a large and strong man, easily able to best most of the other men in Thordstein in combat.

Thirmir seems to always be looking for his son, who frequently runs off to the other side of the island in search of adventure. Because of his son's antics, Thirmir usually has a scowl on his face. Some citizens of Howness have began to wonder if the scowl is frozen in place.
The smell of woodsmoke draws you closer to the dancing fire. The sap of a birch log burns blue at its center.
Change the name of this waypoint into the name of the template you want to use.
